        <detaileddescription>
<para>given not-separating loop on input, finds one or several loops such that 1) resulting loops together with input loop separate a part of mesh, 2) returned loops are oriented the same as input loop (and have the separated mesh part from the other side compared to input loop); 3) the sum of the given metric for their edges is minimal; 4) resulting edges can be only inner to the given region. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
